caption: I’m from Orlando. Went here for my first time and it was sooo good. I got the Pork Banh Mi.
It was amazing...Great flavor and nice place!!!
Fast service. Good environment to eat.
Food tastes good but the quantity is not good
Pretty darn good. Fast and friendly.

This place is delicious! I love how they have sauces at the table to jaz up your bowl. This place gives you silverware and chop sticks. Smells nice in the restaurant and in the ladies room (apparently not in the men's room...) BUUUUUT our server today was rude so that was unfortunate. I'll still go again though for sure. @emmas_oddyssey
This is now my favorite Pho spot!
Great service and staff. The food is very clean and taste great.
Food is flavorful without being overpowering and service is very courteous.
Every time i come to the tampa area i can’t help but stop here no matter what. Genuinely the best food!
The pho was PERFECT. Best soup quality and sides. Best in Tampa. The tarp milk tea was also amazing. Always coming back here now
AMAZING !  Food was flavorful. I live about 2 hours south and I'm heading back there this weekend.  Once you try,  you'll want to go back !!!!
Super cute and comfortable inside, food and boba were amazing! Staff was super friendly and cool as well 🙌
Great Pho
The pho here is reasonable and delicious.

(Translated by Google) The space is very nice, spacious and clean. The attention was excellent and very fast, fresh dishes and freshly cooked food  (Original) El espacio es muy agradable, amplio y limpio. La atención fue excelente y muy rápida, los platos frescos y la comida recién hecha
We got a Bun bowl and we really liked it. Nice decor too
The Chicken Pho was flavorful, although I was a bit disappointed with the portion. Great atmosphere and customer service.
Pho Soup and Muddle Tea are excellent.
Start your day off right with a $5 power bowl! Amazing flavor, fills you up and energizing. All the other food is great too, but love my mornings.

My fav location for vietnamese food. I love this place so much. The service was friendly and sociable. Bring your appetite because portions are filling. I can see why they have a lot of positive reviews.

Vietnamese food at this location - delicious. Service is always awesome even when they have a full house. I've had nothing but pleasant experiences here and plan to keep coming back. The bill was average for the menu.
vietnamese food and the setting at this spot is excellent. Staff is always super even when they have a full house. It has a nice interior.
The food is always fresh and tasty.
vietnamese food, yeah, super yummy. Everyone at our table was enjoying everything. The bill was good for how much you get. Food is like a restaurant in Louisville I liked.

This place was fantastic. I had a bun bowl which was so delicious. I also had an order of gyoza, a coffee, and chai tea latte. All exceeded my expectations. I’d highly recommend eating here. The tables were all at least six feet apart and all staff were wearing masks.
Was ok.  Paid for parking $11
awesome as always
Delicious pho! So convenient next door to WeWork at downtown tampa! Highly recommend— we will be back! 😁 Maybe even the best pho in town!
Great experience. Beef bun bowl outstanding!!!

Ridiculously good and fresh food is served here. The Pho is incredible, the salmon and shrimp/mushroom platters are perfectly cooked and a great bargain, and the Power Bowl is hands down my favorite breakfast. If you like good, inexpensive (but NOT cheap) food, try Fusion Bowl.

One of the best restaurants I have ever been to. I work right around the corner from this place and look forward to having lunch there as often as possible. They have friendly staff and delicious fresh meals. If I could give this place a higher rating I would!
Every order has had fresh, high quality food! Nice prices and friendly staff! 5/5 recommend to anyone seeking delicious, healthy Vietnamese food! Also, the teas are amazing!

This is a small and clean place to grab a healthy and/or good lunch in down town Tampa. The Thai Tea, Vietnamese style rice noodle Bowl,,with Asian cabbage wrap were excellent and the Udon Stir Fried Dish was good as well. You can pick your protein for most of the entrees.I tried this place for the first time downtown, and while it was decent, I probably won't return. The food was good, but not amazing. I prefer other similar places downtown.
One of the best places downtown for breakfast.
Excellent food
Delicious Pho  owl
The people
Very welcoming staff! I had one of the best strawberry ice teas ever! They took care of me even making a special toast for me!! Thank you 🙏
Beautiful food, lovely service and surroundings. Fabulous food and excellent service - so lovely to spend an evening at here.
You and your staff were so very accommodating and informed about our special dietary needs. The food at this restaurant was always delicious!
Nice to have legit Vietnamese in Tampa, very reasonably priced and good atmosphere
Yummy with an Asian flair. Bowls are the best.
Pho was really good, plenty of flavors. Just yum!

This is the best restaurant I tried in Tampa. The Tofu Pho had fresh and various topping that tasted so yummy. The juicy beef was also amazing. This is a perfect restaurant for Asians and Americans. I would like to try undo noodles next time.  My American husband had the beef bun bowl and found it very good. In addition, the price is great and the place is clean.

This restaurant knows how to do pho. They have fresh toppings and if you get it to go they present everything to you separately from the broth which is a plus. Really good taste, great service, the only thing that's inconvenient is the parking but that's because it's downtown, which is expected.
The guy on the regester with tatoos and blonde hair is so disrespectful, doesnt smile doesnt welcome, just so rude. Had this situation with him before.
Authentic broth! Best pho I've had in Tampa

The beef pho was delicious. Nice portion size.. Smart location and pleasant atmosphere. I like that they offered boba tea too. Not too many flavors but the honey green tea was good and mild rather than sickly sweet like some places.

I personally didnt like the food that much, the cabbage tasted weird, but my coworker did. We got the chicken and beef teriyaki. The portions are big, you get a bowl shaped portion of rice, 1/3 of the plate is broccoli and cabbage and carrots, and the other third is chicken.
The BEST Pho in Tampa! Such generous portions and it's always fresh and delicious. HIGHLY recommend this place!!
Great atmosphere. This is a nice, relaxing place to grab a bite. Their selection of drinks is also phenomenal.
Loved it for the very fresh ingredients in the food and how traditional the food is!
Large portion chicken pho, yummy fresh basil and very happy to get a Thai iced tea! A few days back, reminiscing about drinking  Thai tea in NYC !  Just $3.50 for a skinny glass :(
Pho Bowl AMAZING.  Outstanding Customer service

Ideally, Pho is one of those foods that satisfies all the senses: visually appealing, aromatic, savory, with lots oof ingredients to alternately slurp and chew. Fusion Bowl's pho checks all my boxes - a huge bowl of joy! It's the one place I head toi when in downtown Tampa! Love the place. Delicious dishes. Great experience. Already went back again . Same great experience the second time.

Really really really good. The pho was Phonomenal,  the broth was really good, perfectly cooked noodles. The spring roll was on point, great dipping sauce to go with it. Clean place modern open plan and friendly staff. Definitely recommend and I can't wait to go back! The ice green tea was very refreshing.
Coffee is wonderful, avocado spring rolls, udon
Always a good experience.

This place is something else! The girl who served me was the sweetest thing, and the chicken pho was it of this world!! Kind of limey flavor, which was unexpected, but ABSOLUTELY delicious. And the portions were huge for what I paid.  I can't wait to take my friends here!
I loved their beef soup! So delicious:) The best Pho in town, and I’ve tried them all! My only critique is that they are open for dinner! :)
My favorite place for quality vietnamese food. Certainly worth a return trip. It has a good atmosphere.
Good Japanese noodle dishes. Veggies cooked well, not soggy. The tofu was done to perfection.
Large portions for an affordable price! The food is packed with flavor. Customer service was great & my order was out quickly during lunch rush. Will be returning soon.
The food is great and the staff is very nice.
Good rice bowl.
So delicious, fast and filling. Perfect for a quick healthy lunch.
The food was delicious and a very generous portion for the price. Though it was busy, the staff was friendly and the atmosphere was nice. Highly recommend. I will be going back if I'm in the area.
This place was good, but I cant remember what I had...so it doesn't stick out in my head the way some other places do in the area.
Great place for lunch. Quick and attentive staff with a delightful offering of fusion Asian food. Pho, bun bowls ect...
Food is amazing along with the customer service. Great environment, this is the place to eat.
Great food, generous portions, good ambiance.  Ordered a sandwich and a soup on 2 different occasions, both were filled with meat (more than other restaurants tend to do) and were natural.
Pho was premise with everything in it. Not a fan of that as some ingredients I don’t like. Broth was bland and the server (cashier) didn’t know what sambal was.

I've been eating in this restaurant since it opened. All of my meals and drinks have been delicious. What I'm most impressed with is the service. I often order a Breakfast Bowl without bacon and without scallions. They are accommodating and generous. and often remember my preferences. I will continue to enjoy breakfast and lunch meals here. Try the Matcha-honey iced 👍 Thank you, Raquel
Overpriced garbage. I mean, come on. Who charges $5 for a tiny bowl of sliced cucumbers? Fusion Bowl...that's who. Their bowls are meh and their beef is too chewy.
The food is awesome here.  The Korean pork bowl is great and my new fave.  I’m always excited to try something new here.
I love their food. Delicious and flavorful. It is busy because the food is dis.

Service ok. You order at the counter, you pay right away. They prompt you to include service tip. I don't understand how you can pay service fees (tips) before service is even provided... I wanted to say that food was ok, however, both of us had upset stomach within an hour of our lunch. Both of us had beef, but different meals. Hence 2-star rating: don't charge for service fee before service is actually provided, food quality was not to our satisfaction. Although place was busy during lunch time, service was quick, place was clean.

No other pho compares for me.  Broth is AMAZING, always hot, all accompanying goodies are always fresh, no packets of hoisin or siracha-always a container so enough to mix to your liking.  Rice noodles are great and basil fresh and aromatic.  Time and time again my phavorite pho!
Fast service and great Pho!
Friendly great service.  Enjoyed the chicken Pho.  Nice atmosphere.
Fast and attentive services. Super friendly staff members and had a great weekend there.
Food was good but staff were very rude each time an Uber Eats driver came in just to do his job.

This restaurant has excellent food, a diverse menu, fast service, and a really nice and cozy atmosphere especially during the colder months. They were also friendly and able to accommodate specific requests about menu items! I would definitely eat here again.
Always tasty. Quick. Great location to walk to in downtown Tampa.
The chicken soup was out of this world.  Best noddle soup in 47 years!
Deliciously good food!

Tasted great! Definitely will come back. Only complaint I have is they put the greens in your pho instead of on the side like most places. Had to pick them out of my pho. Next time I will tell them not to put it in.
Polite friendly staff. Awesome food
Best asian spots in town.Love the atmosphere and friendly staffs here!

I thought the food here was great, as was the service. It's pretty relaxed, nothing fancy at all, but the food was very tasty. Tried a pho that was great, not super traditional, but still really good, sometimes a bit of variation is a good thing, even in something as tried and tested as a pho. They sure know what they're doing with the flavors in this place!
Excellent food and a affordable price.
Good spring rolls, nice soup. Have to get better at customer service. Bathrooms with a disgusting smell.
Great Banh Mi sandwiches!

Saw this cozy place passing by and ate lunch, we ordered one seafood soup and seafood udon topping it off with a crab Rangoon. With the shrimp over cooked but great amount! Amazing herbs in the pho ginger, beanstalks amazing! Best friend order a chai tea latte and woke right up. Nice chill down place next time a beef pho and latte
Very modern located in the middle of downtown Tampa. They were very friendly and quick for taking a lunch break. Free water in dispenser for customers.
Great food!
BUN Bowl is great...
The food is ok, nothing really blows you away. It's conveniently downtown and affordably priced for the location. There's just so much amazing Vietnamese food around Tampa.
Good place for quick lunch in downtown fast service good staff and good food No parking place get busy really fast in lunch time
Good.
Was there, had their Phone, abit on the salty side, but overall good experience.

The first time we went here we were not impressed.  The udon noodles left much to be desired but the spring rolls were enough to bring us back.  We made the right decision though by giving it another chance for our pho.  Unlike Bamboozle they didn't overload the broth with cilantro, although you may want to pick out the mint leaves but they are big enough to not be an issue.  The spring rolls are big and very leafy if that is your thing.  The peanut sauce is delicious.  I can definitely reccomend this as the best place to go for pho downtown but not so much for other noodle choices.

The crab rangoons were really good they are super generous with the crab. I also got a vermicelli bowl with grilled pork and that had really good flavors. I do wish there was more meat but for the price it was worth it. The fish sauce they use is a little spicy but it all came together really well.
Amazing! The food was great and the atmosphere was so relaxing.
All I did was stop in and get a cup of coffe. It was an adorable little place. Next time I come in I will stop here and try the food. The place has great energies.
Very tasty food, service is good but the restrooms are very smelly. You can smell them from the tables.
Yum! Good and always fresh
I like this place, I will see this place more like a cafe. Rating for the pho, I will give 7 out of 10.
Consistantly good. Great place for lunch!
Nice and clean place, delicious food, variety of selection of foods and quick service
Fresh, clean great food.
Only had Pho but it was great and the atmosphere was comfortable.

Left after seeing the lack cleanliness and hand soap in bathroom. Not confident anyone’s washing their hands there, and bathroom has that bacteria smell of never being cleaned, along with old grime caked around the toilet base and edges around the bathroom. Not worth the risk.
Great food
Very Unprofessional and unorganized
Foods great

You have to try this place! Get the seafood soup bowl, it's a dizzing array of flavors and smells. Very comfortable and clean. Ok I'm just going to talk about that soup. I drove my wife from Bradenton 40 miles away just to try this soup, it's that good!
This place is really good! Teas are good but it’s small so there’s limited seating.
Excellent place
I enjoyed a quick, healthy lunch here on my own--they had great seating for solo diners.
Delisious Boba Thai Tea!!!
Delicious food at a fast pace. Being Vietnamese American myself, I was surprised how much I liked the food!

Excellent Bahn mi sandwiches. Boba is fresh brewed tea, not that franchise type from powder with the heat sealed top. (You know what I'm talking about if you drink boba.) The Earl Grey Lavender Milk Tea is good. It is pretty strong on the lavender, and I love the taste of lavender. I really like that they have real flatware/silverware. (Real plates and silverware as opposed to wasteful paper/plastic/Styrofoam.)
Fast, fresh, delicious
Wide selection, very very good food. Great staff, generous portions, and not very long of a wait time. Definitely worth coming back.
Wonderful place for a quick bite.  The food quality is decent.  It is a little more expensive than other Vietnamese restaurants but this is the only one you can find at downtown Tampa.
The food was fabulous!  Had the lemongrass tofu with vegetables and the seaweed salad.
Amazing place , nice people , the Noddles really good I really recommend it

This place has some awesome Pho and spring rolls! The muddles teas are delicious too and normally I am picky when it comes to tea. I love ordering the edamame or spring rolls when I am looking for something lighter to munch on.
Great breakfast food
Amazing pho
I had the seafood pho and the french viet coffee. Both were delicious, and brought out to me very quickly. I was sincerely impressed.
Food is always fast and delicious. Also a great place to sit and relax or get some work done.
Great bahn mi sandwiches, but took a moderately long time to get them

Ordered the beef pho bowl and pork gyoza. It was amazing. Easily the best pho I've ever had, delicious broth. Gyoza was top 3 at least, but maybe the best too  *Update: This food continues to be amazing as well as the customer service. They forgot our drink one time, gave me the drink and a free dessert too

I love the rice plates with the steamed veggies. Bun Bowl is also an excellent option. Although I wish they had nutritional labels for me to enter in the data to myfitnesspal, I can tell their food is a pretty standard serving size. Fast service, great price, it's my new lunch spot.

I tried a rice dish, beef teriyaki.it was very tasty and was presented very nicely and the portion size was just right. The service was good and was quick. The interior decor was nicely done and a lot of attention to details. I would concider it intomate and cozy and you can dine alone on the bar-like seats by the window.
I ordered the pork gyoza and egg rolls. Both were really nice - I would order them again. The layout on the inside of the restaurant has a casual and cozy feel. Would recommend for lunch.

The food is always tasty and fast here! Great lunch spot in the downtown area! I love the pho, chicken udon and the pork with egg roll bun bowl. They also have great choices for vegetarians as well! I also get the Thai tea which is out of this world!!! This is definitely my go to place for Vietnamese food!!!

I love Asian food. I had passed this place several times as I have walked around downtown Tampa, not giving it much thought. I tried this the other day and I was thoroughly impressed. The food is great and the atmosphere is really nice. I am now upset that I hadn't even given it a try earlier. If you ever get a chance to give this place a shot, I highly recommend it. Worth every penny.

I've had better food on a 14 hour economy flight back from Hong Kong. The beef teriyaki was bland and tough, served next to some blanched cabbage and carrots. This place makes Pei Wei taste and look like a Michelin star restaurant.
Mixture of Asian food. Price is a little high but the food and environment is good. The only Bowl shop near downtown Tampa. Wish they were would add more items to the menu like Ramen for example
Aweful customer service and the food was not authentic. Maybe it's better for the downtown lunch crowd.
Decent Pho, mostly broth but was pretty good. Excellent vibe and service. The food came out in less than a minute.. Great for a quick lunch.
The food is savory! Food portions are more than one needs.
If you want to taste authetic Pho then come here!
Worked well for lunch. I had the udon.  Food was good and was served quickly and the location was convenient.
Good tea and good food. Nice selection of dishes made quickly.
The Beef Teriyaki was excellent!
Best pho in town. Fast service.
Just thought I'd drop a review because I'm CRAVING their udon it's so good! Wish they didn't close so early.

I discovered this place earlier this year just browsing around downtown. Had a craving for some good Asian food. I went in and tried the pho....fell in Love! BEST PHO I'VE EVER HAD! The fusion power bowl is amazing! Literally everything I've tried here has been so delicious and the prices are reasonable. Their boba tea is awesome as well. First time I tried it was there. I always have to come here to get my "Fix" whenever I'm downtown!
I just loved the tuna dish the served
Good food convenient parking
The Pho was amazing, no pork on broth. The mango muddled tea was refreshing as well.
Great place to grab a quick bite for lunch. The portions are quite generous and the teas are very refreshing and different.
Everything was awesome!
Such a cool spot! Love the mood of it! Great pho, nice sized portion. Tuna tartar was delish!
Delicious flavors.
For a place downtown, this hungry intern loves the cheap noodles.
Yummy!!! Loved the food here. Employees are sweet and helpful.
Great food and service one of my down town regular lunch places.

Good pho and quick service. I knocked off one star because the water cups they provide are six ounce cups and, if you like your pho spicy, you have to get up for a refill far more often than if they gave you a normal sized cup.
Fresh, quick, friendly, and delicious.  What else do you need to know?
Yummy and very cute!
Great foodsorst ace to work and he don't wear hats or gloves.and he pays in cash not a taxlayer
Great food, chill atmosphere. I keep coming back. Haven't been disappointed.
Great place for a quick lunch during the week. Prices are slightly higher than other places, food makes up for it.
Food is always great. The staff is wonderful and the Owner is amazing.

I've been here twice with my wife. Both times I've gotten a bun bowl, one beef one pork. They were excellent, especially for the price. They have great customer service and even gave us a free dessert when an error was made.

Meal was decent, but lacking in taste. I had the salmon with a teriyaki sauce (salmon piece was extremely small for price). The springroll appetizer with lemongrass seasoning was a better choice. My girlfriend had the Udon noodle dish and said it was just "OK"... on the flipside, service was solid and the menu was varied.
Good Vietnamese food, good prices.
Very Good fresh Spring rolls!!!
Vegan friendly!  Udon tofu (vegan) & tofu banh mi (also vegan) were very good!

I stopped in for lunch and was pleasantly surprised.  The outside of the building is unremarkable, and over the past several years, has had several failed restaurants in this space.  The inside has been spruced up with minimalist Asian decor, including a lot of live plants and flowers.  The menu includes a lot of various Asian dishes, including pho, udon noodle bowls, and other fast fare.  I chose the udon bowl with chicken, and was not disappointed.  The cost was about what one would expect for a downtown quick lunch.  I will definitely be back.
Awesome food
Good Pho
I LOVE THIS PLACE! They have some of the best authentic foods that taste VERY good. The  sitting area is very clean and it has a natural look and feel to it. I can eat here any time of day.
Modern take on Vietnamese with good Asian fusion options.
My favorite place to eat for lunch downtown. The food is fresh and tastes good. The portions are good too.

Nice place, good service, very good food, Generous portions. The place in downtown Tampa keeps the urban vibe with an understated asian flair. Informal but nice. Chicken Udon was flavorful even though something smelled off-putting when I got my dish. Tasted great though. I would go back.
Great food, great service!
Awesome food!

Bahn Mi sandwiches in downtown Tampa!  In the morning I love to get the Bahn Mi Opla, which comes with a egg cooked sunny side up.  And on cold winter days, the Beef Bowl Noodle Soup. Come early because this place gets packed out for lunch on weekdays! (: (:

Husband and I came here for lunch on a Sunday.  I had the pork and eggroll bun bowl and he had the beef bun bowl.  Both were delicious-- very flavorful.   I would definitely come again to try some other things on their menu!
Great Pho!
Great portions and relaxed atmosphere!

This is a fast food version of Vietnamese cuisine...I ordered the pho and the chicken tastes like it is out of a can. Furthermore the spring rolls had too much lettuce and did not taste fresh. The Thai tea was good.

I usually never write reviews, but I have to tell you that I had stomach ache for a whole week. This place serves food that tastes like nothing. Trust me there are enough Asian places in Tampa that are worth it.

We got here late for lunch (1:30?) and many items were sold out. But what we did get to order was tasty. Pork was better than the beef. The pho was delicious. Would like to come back earlier next time to try some of the other menu items.
Fresh and awesome!
Nice quiet weekday breakfast.

Ordered the gyoza, classic Bahn mi and the pork rice bowl, plus viet affogato and green tea ice cream for dessert. All exceptionally fresh and tasty. Fast and friendly service, too. Will go back whenever in Tampa.
My office colleagues love this place.  Excellent Asian fusion for lunch.
Very disappointed with the Pho

Pho, Bahn Mi, spring rolls, and fresh rolls are great and the staff handles lunch well. It gets pretty slammed midday but I've never seen someone have issues with their orders. I've eaten with people who get the udon and they loved it.

Awesome place. Best pho in town for sure. Great atmosphere. The thai tea is perfect.
The Udon is delicious!
Awesome food, great staff and environment. I come here almost every day.
My first time and it was impressive! I enjoyed that my meal was not drenched in sauce or extremely salty.  I ordered the lemongrass tofu and would definately order it again.
